    "This leads to the optimization problem [GK00] maximize µ T w -γw T Σw subject to",
    "where γ is the risk-aversion parameter that controls the trade-off between risk and return.",
    "Both problems (1) and (2) give the full trade-off curve of Pareto optimal weights, as σ tar or γ vary from 0 to ∞ (although (1) can be infeasible when σ tar is too small).",
    "One advantage of the first formulation (1) is that the parameter σ tar that controls the volatility is interpretable as, simply, the target risk level.",
    "The risk-aversion parameter γ appearing in (2) is less interpretable."
